        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), but it would have been better for his glory if he had acted in a similar spirit.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The earrings of his prey.—Nezem means a ring which, sometimes at least, was worn, especially by women, in the nose (Genesis 24:47; Isaiah 3:21; Ezekiel 16:12; Job 42:11). In the absence of any regular currency, these gold rings served as a sort of coinage.",
        "children": [
